from sklearn.svm import SVR
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error

params = {
    'linear': {},
    'poly': {'coef0': 1.0, 'degree': 2, 'gamma': 0.1}, 
    'rbf': {'gamma': 0.1}
}
cols = ['TotalHour'] + ['lag_%d' % i for i in range(1, 7)]

mae_list = []

for kernel, param in params.items():
    regressor = SVR(kernel=kernel, C=10, **param)
    regressor.fit(X=df_prob4_train[cols], y=df_prob4_train['target'])
    preds = regressor.predict(X=df_prob4_test[cols])
    mae = mean_absolute_error(preds, df_prob4_test['target'])
    mae_list.append((kernel, mae))

]
